      "solution": "/**\n * Can be solved with loops or regex, this example is using regex\n **/\n\nconst N = parseInt(readline());\n\nvar out = \"\";\nfor (let i = 0; i < N; i++) out += readline();\n\nout = out.replace(/([ABC])\\1+/g, (run, char) => (run.length == 1 ? \"\" : run.length) + char);\n\nconsole.log(out);",
